manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Stinger's Pre-Loaded iGO Navigation App SD Card Adding navigation to your ELEV8 or HEIGH10 has never been easier. Optional onboard iGo navigation enhances your ELEV8 or HEIGH10’s driving experience by placing 1000’s of built-in waypoints and landscape data at your fingertips. Detailed landmarks, lane guidance, and complex road junctions are simple to navigate using the intuitive touch panel control. For more information on the iGO nav app, please visit www.iGOnavigation.com FEATURES Built-In Routing Options, Traffic History, And Points Of InterestTraffic is not a problemRealistic, Detailed VisualizationGuidance EverywhereSearch With Real-Time Guidance UpdatesNo Cellular Signal RequiredPerfect GPS Upgrade For Your Stinger Radio Includes Navigation Micro SD CardMicro SD Card Adaptor

Features Different Routing Options No more nasty surprises. Our routing is among the most consistent on the market! Select the best route according to your preferences and vehicle profile, and then compare the route alternatives! Fast, easy, green - whatever you prefer. Easy To Install Slide the Micro SD card in the brain of your new ELEV8 or HEIGH10, follow the setup prompts on your radio's touchscreen. And that's it! Realistic Visualization Amazing 3-dimensional imagery helps you better understand your surroundings. Detailed landmarks and city models act as reliable points of referent and accurate depictions of lanes, tunnels and complex junctions make the world around you easier to navigate and understand. Guidance Everywhere We help you navigate a labyrinth of lanes, roads, signposts, and junctions with precise maneuver instructions. This way, you’ll never be caught off guard. But for the inertial surprise or mistake, we instantly recalculate your route and get you back on track.

Search Like A Pro Simply search for addresses or among thousands of POIs (points of interest, including cafés, museums, bars, restaurants, gas stations, and many more along the route! Only know part of the address? We’ll help you figure out the rest! You can search online when a network connection is available. Traffic is not a problem either! Historical (statistical) traffic data is considered when calculating your route.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 1, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars If You've Invested In A Awesome Stinger Infotainment System....This Is A Must Have Accessory!
reviews.reviewText: I received the Stinger Infotainment System Stereo Upgrade for my 2016 Rubicon Wrangler as birthday gift from my wife. While the new system with it's 10" Screen was amazing...I'm the kind of guy that wants all the full functionality of what this incredible system can offer so I purchased this Navigation Chip which simply slides into the front of the Radio Brain Unit behind the screen. It instantly updates and "BAM" you have up to date navigation for all of the United States in moments! If you have the Stinger Infotainment System and want all of the options...you must purchase and install this navigation card. Additionally, the team at Stinger is amazing, professional and so knowledgeable about installation tips and guidance. Best Ever upgrade for your Jeep Wrangler! Thank you Stinger Team!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 25, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Seller Good - Product Overpriced
reviews.reviewText: Can’t sing the seller, review is for Stinger and Naviextras. Overpriced big time and didn’t come updated with latest maps. Download the tool and still won’t recognize the SD card even though I can see it in my files (and drill through). Probably a windows deal where it won’t run on Windows 11. Hard pass, do not purchase the Nav card and just use CarPlay or android auto

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Here is how you update!!!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this just to have as a backup if I ever needed it. Updating the maps really was frustrating so I am going to share and hopefully help someone. The directions say to update before putting in the Heigh10, THAT IS WRONG!!! You need to install the card and then go to settings and click on update iGo. Once you have done that you can use the Naviextra Toolbox and update on the PC. Hope this saves someone the frustration that I went through.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 10, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Sinal on GPS keeps going in and out. Going to recheck connection. I think the GPS receiver may have to be move to a higher location instead of where stinger install video said to put it. Will keep you all updated weather it works or not.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars This is HORRIBLE
reviews.reviewText: My professional installers now gone back and forth for two days with Stinger. The GPS does not track properly and jumps around. If there is a side road on the track, it will jump to it and "RECALCULATING". The software was updated properly, even working with tech support. The antenna is not near my Sirius antenna. NOTHING we do fixes this issue. This was a huge purchase point for me. Now, I have a $1500 device that does not function as it should. The $150 purchase of the iGO navigation card is a waste. I am super surprised that this product can even be released. I'm not the only one this happens to. I will leave the card in, in hopes someone at Stinger will get their product fixed. But for now, I would NOT RECOMMEND this product at all.

reviews.reviewText: Pop it in the head unit, turn the radio on....boom...instant navigation. Do some set up tweaks and you have a great nav tool.
